466
00:29:47,194 --> 00:29:49,077
No, b-because you lied your way in.

467
00:29:49,102 --> 00:29:50,952
- Not how I remember it.
- What happened...

468
00:29:50,977 --> 00:29:52,835
And I've got witnesses to back me up.

469
00:29:52,860 --> 00:29:54,721
Do you like being an
Air Force Captain, huh?

470
00:29:54,746 --> 00:29:56,586
You think the United
States wants to bring action

471
00:29:56,611 --> 00:29:58,483
against an old man in a wheelchair?!

472
00:29:58,508 --> 00:30:00,601
He was standing on TV.

473
00:30:00,626 --> 00:30:02,070
- He wasn't even in a wheelchair!
- Well, yeah.

474
00:30:02,095 --> 00:30:03,366
Well, periodically, he is.

475
00:30:03,391 --> 00:30:04,405
And when he shows up in court,

476
00:30:04,430 --> 00:30:06,196
you better believe
he'll be in a wheelchair!

477
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:08,180
Right, because you're an
ambulance-chasing piece of shit,

478
00:30:08,205 --> 00:30:09,562
'cause you're all the same...
you're the same as all the others.

479
00:30:09,587 --> 00:30:10,675
Always on a high horse.

480
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:13,022
Always trying to make
me feel like I'm...

481
00:30:20,636 --> 00:30:23,175
Look, um, I'm a lawyer,

482
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:25,292
and this is what I
do all day, every day,

483
00:30:25,317 --> 00:30:26,910
so h-how about this?

484
00:30:26,935 --> 00:30:29,406
I-I won't fly jet planes...

485
00:30:29,971 --> 00:30:31,480
you, uh, stay out of court.

486
00:30:31,505 --> 00:30:33,183
Does that sound good?

487
00:30:34,990 --> 00:30:36,355
[Scoffs]

488
00:30:37,683 --> 00:30:39,870
You know, guys like you...

489
00:30:40,661 --> 00:30:43,238
you think you're so damn smart,

490
00:30:43,764 --> 00:30:46,644
and you think you don't have
to play straight with anybody.

491
00:30:47,619 --> 00:30:49,613
The wheel is gonna turn.

492
00:30:49,785 --> 00:30:51,628
It always does.

493
00:30:52,964 --> 00:30:55,285
[Door opens, creaks]

494
00:31:06,297 --> 00:31:07,752
